cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with automatic pain intensity estimation from facial images in videos. The use of a recurrent convolutional neural network also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the focus on healthcare and medical applications could place it in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of facial images and video data could also suggest the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of regression for continuous pain intensity estimation could place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
